summary:
The Security Council:

 Requests the Group of Experts to: 
- Keep the Committee updated on its activities (f); 
- Provide evidence of violations of measures imposed by resolutions 1572 (2004) and 1643 (2005) (g); 
- Cooperate with other relevant groups of experts (h); 
- Monitor individual measures set out in resolutions 1572 (2004) (i);

 Requests the Secretary-General, French Government, and Kimberley Process to communicate information to the Security Council, through the Committee, on the supply of arms and related materiel to Côte d’Ivoire and production and illicit export of diamonds;

 Urges all States, UN bodies, and organizations to cooperate fully with the Committee, Group of Experts, UNOCI, and French forces;

 Underlines its readiness to impose targeted measures against individuals who threaten the peace and national reconciliation process in Côte d’Ivoire, obstruct UNOCI or French forces, or commit serious human rights violations;

 Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
